        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(tools): honor config apiKey in media tool preflight",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add a shared `hasProviderAuthForTool()` helper that accepts existing env/profile auth **or** `models.providers.*.apiKey`.\n- Route image, PDF, and generation tool model/list preflight through that helper so custom providers with config-backed keys can be auto-selected.\n- Thread `workspaceDir` through generation tool model/list availability paths for consistent auth context.\n- **Scope note:** this replaces #85356 with a smaller Plan B fix. It does **not** pull in `hasRuntimeAvailableProviderAuth`, `aws-sdk` rejection, or Bedrock follow-up commits.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/tools/model-config.helpers.test.ts src/agents/tools/media-tool-shared.test.ts src/agents/tools/image-tool.test.ts src/agents/tools/pdf-tool.model-config.test.ts`\n\nBehavior addressed: custom provider `models.providers.*.apiKey` is honored during image/PDF/generation tool model preflight.\nReal environment tested: local Linux worktree on latest `main`.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: focused Vitest files above.\nEvidence after fix: hatchery/custom-provider regression tests pass; no aws-sdk/Bedrock logic added.\nObserved result after fix: config-backed providers pass preflight without env key or auth profile.\nWhat was not tested: full repository check, live provider calls, Bedrock/aws-sdk scenarios.\n\nSupersedes: #85356",
        "branch": "fix/media-tool-config-auth-plan-b",
